//sed cmd

sed 's/old/new'  file replaces first occurence

sed 's/old/new/g'  file replaces globally


sed '/search/s/old/new'  file if search word there is then replaces

i-before line.a-after,d-delete
sed -i '1i  whatever u want to insert'   file--before line 1 it will be inserted
